"```sql\nSELECT \n    SUM(t.Amount) AS TotalAmountSpent\nFROM \n    transactions_1k t\nJOIN \n    yearmonth ym ON t.CustomerID = ym.CustomerID\nWHERE \n    t.CustomerID = 38508\n    AND ym.Date = '201201';\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the total amount spent by customer with ID 38508 at gas stations in January 2012. It joins the `transactions_1k` table with the `yearmonth` table using the `CustomerID` and filters the results for the specified customer and date."